summary: The document 230.505 CFR pertains to the Code of Federal Regulations concerning the standards and procedures for the protection of human subjects in research conducted or supported by the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS). It outlines the requirements for informed consent, ensuring that participants are fully aware of the nature, risks, and benefits of the research before agreeing to take part.
